'''Tekkatho''' ([[Burmese language|Burmese]]: {{IPA|[tɛ̀ʔ gà dàu]}}) means [[university]] in [[Burmese language]], which derives from the name [[Taxila|Taxila University]], located in modern-day [[Pakistan]]. In colonial times, [[writer]]s, [[artist]]s, and [[photographer]]s who had studied at university used Tekkatho as a title in front of their [[penname]]s.

